Odysseas Elytis was a Greek poet born in 1911 in Crete. He received many honors for his poetry including the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1979. Elytis wrote poems inspired by themes of the sun, sea, and love. He is considered one of the most significant Greek poets for rejuvenating Greek poetry and connecting his works deeply to Greek culture, people, and spirit.
